This paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms for discovering heavy hitters in user-generated data streams. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Given the focus on privacy and data streams, cs.DB and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of sampling and analysis of large-scale Twitter data also suggests relevance to cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.SI.
